==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Libidinous
<hw>Li*bid"i*nous</hw> <pr>(-n⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>libidinosus</ets>, fr. <ets>libido</ets>, <ets>libidinis</ets>,
pleasure, desire, lust, fr. <ets>libet</ets>, <ets>lubet</ets>, it
pleases: cf. F. <ets>libidineux</ets>. See <er>Lief</er>.]</ety>
<def>Having lustful desires; characterized by lewdness; sensual;
lascivious.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Li*bid"i*nous*ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos> -- <wf>Li*bid"i*nous*ness</wf>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Lewd; lustful; lascivious; unchaste; impure;
sensual; licentious; lecherous; salacious.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>libido</ent>⟦br⟧
